  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>chicken breast<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;and cook for 3 min on each side or until golden</p>\r\n<p>Once golden, reduce the heat to medium, add&nbsp;a splash of <strong>water</strong> and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until the <strong>chicken</strong> is cooked through</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1079.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1079.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1079.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1079.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1079.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Cut the <strong>pak choi</strong> in half, separating the <strong>white</strong> and<strong> green parts</strong></p>\r\n<p>Set the <strong>green tops</strong> aside and cut the <strong>whites</strong> into bite-sized pieces&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1079.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1079.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1079.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1079.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1079.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a second large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong>&nbsp;vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>ground&nbsp;turmeric</strong> and cook for 30 sec</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and <strong>Thai green curry paste</strong> and cook for 2 min</p>\r\n<p>Reduce the heat to medium-low, add the<strong> white pak choi</strong>&nbsp;with a generous pinch of <strong>salt&nbsp;</strong>and cook for 3 min or until the<strong> pak choi</strong> is tender</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
